<p><span class="anchor" id="appendix-2"></span><h3>Appendix 2. Bulk
density calculations.</h3></p>
<p>Refer to McKenzie <em>et al.</em> (2002) for further details.</p>
<ol type="1">
<li><p>Measure, with calipers, the internal dimensions (diameter =
L<sub>1</sub>; length = L<sub>2</sub>) of a coring ring in metres to
determine the volume (V<sub>1</sub>). Each dimension should be measured
several times</p></li>
<li><p>Ensure the soil level of each intact core is trimmed level with
the ends of the coring ring. Trim using a sharp knife if
necessary.</p></li>
<li><p>Weigh a dry, oven proof container (e.g. an aluminium dish) with a
laboratory balance with accuracy to ±0.01 g (10 mg; weight
W<sub>1</sub>) for each core.</p></li>
<li><p>Take each core and push all of the soil out of the coring ring
into an oven-proof container. Carefully clean all soil out of each
coring ring. Weigh each container and soil (W<sub>2</sub>).</p></li>
<li><p>Dry the soil in the containers in a well ventilated oven at 105°C
until the weight is constant (approximately 48 hours).</p></li>
<li><p>Cool in a desiccator before weighing each container and oven-dry
soil (W<sub>3</sub>).</p></li>
<li><p>Calculate the bulk density of each sample using the following
equation:</p>
<br><img alt="bulkD" id="bulk-density" height="100" src="https://w3id.org/tern/static/dawe-rlp/latest/soil/Bulk_density.png" width="500"/></br>
</ol>
<p>Bulk density samples containing coarse fragments:</p>
<p>The presence of coarse fragments (i.e. particles &gt;2mm diameter) in
soil has a significant effect on bulk density. If the sample contains
coarse fragments, the mass and volume of coarse fragments, gross bulk
density of the soil with coarse fragments, and bulk density of the
fine-earth fraction (i.e. bulk density of soil without the coarse
fragment component) need to be considered (McKenzie <em>et al.</em>
2002).</p>
<ol type="1">
<li><p>After drying and cooling (see above), separate the coarse
fragment component of each sample by sieving through a 2 mm
sieve.</p></li>
<li><p>Weigh the fine earth and container (W<sub>4</sub>) and coarse
fragments and container (W<sub>5</sub>) of each sample
separately.</p></li>
<li><p>Determine the volume of the coarse fragments (V<sub>2</sub>) of
each sample by displacement of water.</p></li>
<li><p>Calculate the of the gross bulk density of each sample using the
following equation:</p>
<br><img alt="bulkD" id="bulk-density" height="100" src="https://w3id.org/tern/static/dawe-rlp/latest/soil/Gross_BD.png" width="400"/></br>
<li><p>Calculate the of the fine earth bulk density of each sample using
the following equation:</p>
<br><img alt="bulkD" id="bulk-density" height="100" src="https://w3id.org/tern/static/dawe-rlp/latest/soil/Fine_earth_BD.png" width="400"/></br>
</ol>
